            "What controls ADH secretion?",                                                                                          ##               Osmoreceptors in the hypothalamus (mainly) and baroreceptors in the carotid sinus and aortic arch (less important) regulate ADH secretion. Osmoreceptors respond to changes in plasma osmolality, while baroreceptors respond to changes in blood volume and pressure. Increased osmolality or decreased blood volume/pressure stimulates ADH release, Increases the permeability of collecting ducts by an effect on the aquaporin 2 Receptor so that water enters into the hypertonic interstitium of the renal pyramids, Glycogenolysis in liver, Stimulation of clotting factor production.                  
