            "What factors affect the concentration of 2,3-DPG?",                                                                         #            Growth hormons, thyroid hormons, acidosis, 2,3-DPG is produced in red blood cells (RBCs) from 1,3-bisphosphoglycerate during glycolysis. It binds to deoxygenated haemoglobin and stabilises the T-state, thereby reducing haemoglobin's affinity for oxygen and facilitating oxygen release to tissues. Factors that increase 2,3-DPG levels include chronic hypoxia (e.g., high altitude), anaemia, and certain medical conditions. Conversely, factors that decrease 2,3-DPG levels include alkalosis, blood transfusions with stored blood (which has reduced 2,3-DPG), and certain medications.          
