            "Describe the formation and circulation of cerebrospinal fluid.",                                                            ##           Choroid plexus in the lateral ventricles and partly from third and fourth ventricles, passage of CSF from third to fourth ventricle through aqueduct foramen. Ultimately CSF leaves the fourth ventricle via the foramina of Magendie (in the Midline) and Luschka (Laterally) thence reaching the cisterns and bathing the spinal cord and the brain, 0.3 ml/min (500–600 ml/day). Total volume is 100–150 ml. 85–90% of CSF is reabsorbed through arachnoid villi.
