            "Outline the anatomy of the larynx.",                                                                                       #             Complex hollow structure in the anterior neck at C3-C5, framework of nine articulating cartilages connected by ligaments and muscles. It connects inferior part of the pharynx to the trachea (lined by a ciliated mucous membrane). It functions as a sphincter protecting from aspiration, esp. during swallowing. It is also the organ of phonation (voice production) and is required for coughing and straining.
