            "What are affinity and intrinsic activity?",                                                                                 #            Affinity is the strength of binding between a drug and its receptor, while intrinsic activity (also known as efficacy) is the ability of a drug to produce a biological response once it has bound to the receptor. A drug with high affinity binds strongly to its receptor, while a drug with high intrinsic activity produces a strong response when it binds to the receptor. Some drugs may have high affinity but low intrinsic activity (antagonists), while others may have both high affinity and high intrinsic activity (full agonists).          
